mern (1) : https://jasonwatmore.com/post/2019/11/18/react-nodejs-on-aws-how-to-deploy-a-mern-stack-app-to-amazon-ec2

only react (worked) : https://dev.to/xarala221/the-easiest-way-to-deploy-a-react-web-application-2l8a

mern (2) : https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=c7It9bBM8IM


1) install node,mongo,nginx,etc..... on server
2) pull project to opt/bacend opt/fronted
3) go to each project install necessaity things npm i
3) create folder mkdir home/ubuntu/app-deploy
4) cp -R opt/frontend/build home/ubuntu/app-deploy (copy build)
5) setup nginx etc/nginx/sites-availabl/make-a-file (nginx config)
6) setup sites-enabled sudo ln -s /etc/nginx/sites-available/react_counter /etc/nginx/sites-enabled
7) test nginx config. sudo nginx -t
8) restart nginx. sudo systemctl restart nginx
